Specify the size of the memory holding the information for page
access in the data cache.
During each page access of a transaction, one entry must be made 
in this area. The necessary size depends on the degree of 
transaction parallelism and the average number of simultaneously
active SELECT queries (CURSORs) per transaction.
The default size is sufficient in most cases.
This cache is in shared memory.


   -	Command Line Syntax :   ss=<size in KB>
